@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="container">
    <h1 class="fw-bold mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">Last updated: @DateTime.Today.ToString("dd MMM yyyy")</p>

    <p>We respect your privacy. This policy explains what we collect, why we collect it, and how we protect it.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Information we collect</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Contact details (name, email, phone) provided when booking or contacting us.</li>
        <li>Appointment information (service, date/time, notes you choose to share).</li>
        <li>Website usage data (basic analytics and cookies to keep the site working).</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-4">How we use your information</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>To manage bookings, send confirmations and reminders.</li>
        <li>To respond to enquiries and provide support.</li>
        <li>To improve our services and website experience.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-4">How we protect your data</h5>
    <p>We use reasonable administrative and technical safeguards. Access is limited to staff who need it to perform their work.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Sharing</h5>
    <p>We don’t sell your data. We only share with service providers that help us run our business (e.g. email and hosting) and only as necessary.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Your choices</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>You may access, correct, or request deletion of your personal information.</li>
        <li>You may opt out of non-essential communications at any time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5 class="mt-4">Contact</h5>
    <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hello@vitalscan.com">hello@vitalscan.com</a>.</p>
</div>
